text: Papago may refer to: * An archaic term for Tohono Oʼodham people * An archaic term for the language spoken by the Tohono Oʼodham people * Papago (moth), a genus of geometer moths * Papago Freeway, I-10 through Phoenix, Arizona * Papago Freeway Tunnel, a tunnel in Arizona * Papago Park, a park in Arizona * Papago, a village in the northern part of the island of Saipan * Naver Papago, a translation service * , a ship of the U.S. Navy * Great Papago Escape, a mass escape by Axis P.O.W.s from an American facility during World War Two
title: Papago
